The paper focuses on learning rich representations using deep generative models, specifically variational auto-encoders (VAE). This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses two benchmark datasets, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of disentanglement metrics, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
